1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:06,600
Characters, actions, places, occupations,
and events in this series

2
00:00:06,600 --> 00:00:09,280
are fictional and created for entertainment purposes only.

3
00:00:09,280 --> 00:00:13,920
They are not intended to urge or promote any behavior in the series.

4
00:00:13,920 --> 00:00:16,520
Viewer discretion is advised.

5
00:00:16,520 --> 00:00:18,280
I know I was too harsh on you.

6
00:00:18,280 --> 00:00:20,680
If you slept with Shasha to spite me,

7
00:00:20,800 --> 00:00:22,200
you are so mean.

8
00:00:22,400 --> 00:00:26,040
I hope I will have a chance
to have a meal with your family one day.

9
00:00:26,440 --> 00:00:29,120
I want you to take care of me.

10
00:00:29,160 --> 00:00:30,760
Do you want to be my personal assistant?

11
00:00:31,200 --> 00:00:32,800
I never thought I would meet you here.

12
00:00:33,360 --> 00:00:34,680
Is that woman your girlfriend?

13
00:00:34,720 --> 00:00:36,600
Don’t become another disappointment
in our family.

14
00:00:36,760 --> 00:00:37,760
Are you blackmailing me?

15
00:00:37,800 --> 00:00:40,680
Let’s call it a business negotiation.

16
00:00:41,560 --> 00:00:44,880
Ton is influential in this industry.

17
00:00:45,880 --> 00:00:48,320
If he tells you to do something, do it.

18
00:00:48,360 --> 00:00:49,360
Understand?

19
00:00:51,160 --> 00:00:54,840
Whether you become famous or not
depends on today.

20
00:01:00,480 --> 00:01:03,480
Shasha, are you listening?

21
00:01:06,920 --> 00:01:07,680
Sha!

22
00:01:08,520 --> 00:01:09,240
Yes?

23
00:01:11,560 --> 00:01:12,840
Listen.

24
00:01:13,360 --> 00:01:15,880
Your mom entrusted you to me.

25
00:01:16,400 --> 00:01:19,480
I have to make you famous.

26
00:01:20,800 --> 00:01:25,560
If you do well today, we’ll all be set.

27
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:29,080
Then why didn’t my mom come?

28
00:01:30,039 --> 00:01:32,360
She’s abroad with your stepfather.

29
00:01:33,000 --> 00:01:36,320
Just focus on working
and saving a lot of money.

30
00:01:36,640 --> 00:01:39,160
You can go to her anytime.

31
00:01:43,360 --> 00:01:44,560
Turn around.

32
00:01:50,759 --> 00:01:51,440
Slip it off.

33
00:01:56,280 --> 00:01:57,560
Do I have to?

34
00:01:58,600 --> 00:02:00,480
You want to be a model, don’t you?

35
00:02:04,080 --> 00:02:05,560
Don’t waste my time.

36
00:02:06,240 --> 00:02:06,840
Take it off.

37
00:02:12,200 --> 00:02:13,760
(Just focus on saving a lot of money.)

38
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:16,440
(You can go to her anytime.)

39
00:02:17,800 --> 00:02:19,360
Being this shy,

40
00:02:20,360 --> 00:02:21,840
you probably don’t know that

41
00:02:21,880 --> 00:02:25,680
backstage at runway shows,
models change in front of the crew.

42
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:28,360
Everything has to be fast.

43
00:02:28,600 --> 00:02:31,280
If you’re like this, it’ll be difficult.

44
00:02:55,800 --> 00:02:56,680
Lift your skirt.

45
00:03:02,440 --> 00:03:06,680
If you want to be a model,
you have to be bold to go far.

46
00:03:24,560 --> 00:03:25,520
Higher.

47
00:03:26,440 --> 00:03:27,240
Lift it more.

48
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:34,760
Shasha.

49
00:04:36,200 --> 00:04:37,159
Shasha!

50
00:04:37,760 --> 00:04:39,240
Why do you look like such a mess?

51
00:04:39,520 --> 00:04:40,360
Mm…

52
00:04:41,400 --> 00:04:43,159
You have work today, you know that.

53
00:04:43,800 --> 00:04:46,680
Get up, Shasha. You have a shoot today.

54
00:04:48,480 --> 00:04:50,880
Can you cancel it for me?

55
00:04:50,880 --> 00:04:52,760
Any excuse will do.

56
00:04:53,080 --> 00:04:54,280
Stop being selfish.

57
00:04:54,920 --> 00:04:57,120
The whole crew would have to stop
because of you alone?

58
00:04:59,120 --> 00:04:59,880
Get up.

59
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:02,520
One.

60
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:05,400
Two.

61
00:05:07,720 --> 00:05:08,680
Three!

62
00:05:09,040 --> 00:05:10,080
Ugh…

63
00:05:15,680 --> 00:05:17,280
Why do you look so worn out?

64
00:05:19,800 --> 00:05:21,160
I’ll prepare a mask for you.

65
00:05:23,080 --> 00:05:24,400
You reek of wine.

66
00:05:24,440 --> 00:05:25,760
Did you drink or bathe in it?

67
00:05:26,880 --> 00:05:28,200
Go take a shower.

68
00:05:28,440 --> 00:05:29,720
Can I sleep a bit more?

69
00:05:29,720 --> 00:05:30,840
Go shower.

70
00:05:31,240 --> 00:05:32,360
And clean yourself properly.

71
00:05:32,600 --> 00:05:34,080
Don’t smell like wine.

72
00:05:34,640 --> 00:05:35,640
It’s embarrassing.

73
00:05:37,000 --> 00:05:38,280
Go shower.

74
00:05:42,640 --> 00:05:46,280
Everyone,
this is Baipor, my younger sister.

75
00:05:47,200 --> 00:05:48,760
She’s interning as a creative.

76
00:05:49,159 --> 00:05:50,760
Please teach her.

77
00:05:51,200 --> 00:05:54,080
If she messes up, feel free to scold her.

78
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:55,600
Don’t hold back just because of me.

79
00:05:57,640 --> 00:06:00,280
Nice to meet you. Please guide me.

80
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:03,760
You can scold me, but gently, please.

81
00:06:03,960 --> 00:06:05,160
My heart is this tiny.

82
00:06:10,640 --> 00:06:13,320
Min, are you listening?

83
00:06:13,720 --> 00:06:14,760
Yeah.

84
00:06:16,440 --> 00:06:18,080
You can talk to me anytime.

85
00:06:18,400 --> 00:06:19,960
Prim’s sister is like my own sister.

86
00:06:20,360 --> 00:06:22,000
But don’t be clingy with your partner
like she is.

87
00:06:22,840 --> 00:06:24,920
I said scold her, not me.

88
00:06:26,200 --> 00:06:28,440
Don’t worry. I’m not in a relationship.

89
00:06:28,880 --> 00:06:30,960
Having one distracts you.

90
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,960
I’ll focus on work for now.

91
00:06:34,000 --> 00:06:34,880
You’re just as bad.

92
00:06:35,480 --> 00:06:37,880
Alright, everyone, it’s lunch break.

93
00:06:38,080 --> 00:06:39,880
We’ll continue the meeting after.

94
00:06:42,600 --> 00:06:43,960
Do you want to eat together, Prim?

95
00:06:44,440 --> 00:06:46,920
Uh, I need to discuss work with Min first.

96
00:06:47,880 --> 00:06:49,000
Do you want to come with us?

97
00:06:49,120 --> 00:06:49,760
Sure.

98
00:06:50,680 --> 00:06:51,560
Don’t be stubborn.

99
00:06:59,600 --> 00:07:00,840
What’s wrong with you?

100
00:07:00,960 --> 00:07:02,160
Fighting with your young girlfriend?

101
00:07:02,480 --> 00:07:05,480
Yeah. She hasn’t replied for a week.

102
00:07:05,920 --> 00:07:07,680
You’re not clear with her.

103
00:07:08,480 --> 00:07:09,880
I’d feel hurt too.

104
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:12,840
Back then, I saw you bring Park home

105
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:16,160
and post it all over social media,
showing off to all the single people.

106
00:07:16,640 --> 00:07:17,960
It’s not that simple.

107
00:07:18,480 --> 00:07:20,040
I have another social circle.

108
00:07:20,080 --> 00:07:23,640
If I come out as a lesbian,
people will gossip.

109
00:07:24,960 --> 00:07:27,800
So you care more about gossip
than Praew’s feelings?

110
00:07:30,760 --> 00:07:34,280
Min, I totally understand you.

111
00:07:35,120 --> 00:07:37,040
But you’re not the only one
who needs to adjust.

112
00:07:37,040 --> 00:07:38,680
She does too.

113
00:07:39,920 --> 00:07:42,520
Ask yourself what you want.

114
00:07:43,159 --> 00:07:45,520
And be clear with Praew.

115
00:07:46,120 --> 00:07:47,159
Got it?

116
00:07:48,159 --> 00:07:48,960
Let’s go

117
00:07:51,080 --> 00:07:51,880
Hurry up.

118
00:08:02,880 --> 00:08:04,440
Is this okay, Prim?

119
00:08:04,720 --> 00:08:06,480
Anything you want me to fix?

120
00:08:07,160 --> 00:08:09,160
I tried my best for you.

121
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:12,760
Thank you so much.

122
00:08:13,040 --> 00:08:14,960
The previous AE spoiled clients too much.

123
00:08:15,000 --> 00:08:16,360
Work wasn’t fun at all.

124
00:08:16,720 --> 00:08:18,320
I couldn’t put anything into the work.

125
00:08:18,320 --> 00:08:19,560
It was all about selling.

126
00:08:20,640 --> 00:08:22,680
I understand your creative style, Prim.

127
00:08:23,000 --> 00:08:27,240
I’ll balance bringing in
a lot of profits for the company

128
00:08:27,280 --> 00:08:29,160
and keeping you happy.

129
00:08:30,240 --> 00:08:33,480
But can you fix this part for me?

130
00:08:34,600 --> 00:08:36,080
I’m afraid the client might misunderstand.

131
00:08:36,120 --> 00:08:37,760
We don’t have that much budget.

132
00:08:38,159 --> 00:08:42,280
Well, is it this part?

133
00:08:50,200 --> 00:08:52,440
Oops, sorry.

134
00:08:53,040 --> 00:08:54,160
Anything else?

135
00:08:57,320 --> 00:08:58,880
No, that’s it.

136
00:08:59,840 --> 00:09:03,160
Okay, I’ll revise it
and let you check again.

137
00:09:06,680 --> 00:09:08,760
I still have a lot to learn.

138
00:09:09,040 --> 00:09:10,720
Thank you for teaching me, Prim.

139
00:09:17,880 --> 00:09:19,360
Good afternoon.

140
00:09:24,800 --> 00:09:25,800
Oh, Bambi?

141
00:09:25,840 --> 00:09:27,360
You didn’t tell me you were coming.

142
00:09:28,400 --> 00:09:29,760
I wanted to surprise you,

143
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:31,680
but got surprised instead.

144
00:09:36,840 --> 00:09:38,960
She brought work for me for proof.

145
00:09:39,440 --> 00:09:41,840
She even got us a new client.
She’s great at pitching.

146
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:45,560
That’s good for your company.

147
00:09:47,240 --> 00:09:50,480
Just keep it about work, nothing else.

148
00:09:51,400 --> 00:09:52,880
I’m focused on work.

149
00:09:53,280 --> 00:09:55,280
I barely have time for my partner.

150
00:09:56,120 --> 00:09:58,280
Oh? You have a partner?

151
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:01,840
Yes, but it feels like I don’t.

152
00:10:02,040 --> 00:10:03,600
We argue a lot lately.

153
00:10:03,960 --> 00:10:08,560
Then try focusing on your relationship.

154
00:10:09,160 --> 00:10:11,160
Pay attention to your own matters.

155
00:10:11,480 --> 00:10:12,840
Maybe you’ll love each other more.

156
00:10:13,280 --> 00:10:14,520
You can manage your time.

157
00:10:14,960 --> 00:10:16,120
Prim won’t mind.

158
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:22,000
Thank you.

159
00:10:22,320 --> 00:10:27,360
I hope my relationship becomes
as happy as yours.

160
00:10:40,280 --> 00:10:42,680
I knew it. She’s suspicious.

161
00:10:44,280 --> 00:10:45,960
She totally wants you.

162
00:10:46,440 --> 00:10:48,960
Maybe she planned it
since that badminton court day.

163
00:10:49,000 --> 00:10:51,240
Come on, you’re overthinking it.

164
00:10:51,520 --> 00:10:53,560
No one tries that hard.

165
00:10:54,320 --> 00:10:55,880
You don’t know anything.

166
00:10:56,000 --> 00:10:58,040
Back when I wanted you to hit on me,

167
00:10:58,080 --> 00:11:01,600
I used to hang around your faculty often
to get you to talk to me.

168
00:11:02,080 --> 00:11:05,560
When you like someone,
you try to be near them.

169
00:11:06,200 --> 00:11:08,160
Wow, I just found out.

170
00:11:08,480 --> 00:11:09,840
So you liked me first?

171
00:11:13,600 --> 00:11:14,360
No.

172
00:11:15,240 --> 00:11:18,320
Technically, you chased me first.

173
00:11:18,520 --> 00:11:19,800
But you just confessed.

174
00:11:21,000 --> 00:11:21,680
So?

175
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:27,080
Fine. I liked you first.

176
00:11:27,800 --> 00:11:30,480
So you’re mine now.

177
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:32,080
No one else can touch you.

178
00:11:32,440 --> 00:11:35,960
If they try, they’ll meet my vicious side.

179
00:11:39,000 --> 00:11:39,840
Like this.

180
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:41,480
Then eat me first?

181
00:11:44,200 --> 00:11:45,240
I’m always ready.

182
00:12:08,160 --> 00:12:09,360
Let me check the photos.

183
00:12:13,240 --> 00:12:15,160
Yeah, this works. Thanks.

184
00:12:16,680 --> 00:12:18,960
No problem.
Let me know if you need anything.

185
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:23,880
I thought you’d forget me
now that you’re dating a senior.

186
00:12:24,520 --> 00:12:25,680
What are you talking about?

187
00:12:25,960 --> 00:12:27,480
I’m not like that.

188
00:12:29,040 --> 00:12:30,160
How'd it go?

189
00:12:30,200 --> 00:12:32,240
Dating someone
who's never dated a girl before?

190
00:12:33,520 --> 00:12:34,480
It’s good.

191
00:12:35,000 --> 00:12:36,840
But she doesn’t want to go public.

192
00:12:37,560 --> 00:12:38,880
She’s still not ready?

193
00:12:39,360 --> 00:12:40,920
She’s grown. What’s she afraid of?

194
00:12:41,280 --> 00:12:42,960
Then when will she be ready?

195
00:12:43,200 --> 00:12:45,240
Months? Years?

196
00:12:47,720 --> 00:12:50,800
Forget it. It’s probably not that long.

197
00:12:51,240 --> 00:12:52,520
How do you know?

198
00:12:53,040 --> 00:12:56,240
She might just be testing you,
then go back to a guy

199
00:12:57,040 --> 00:12:59,680
or find someone better.

200
00:13:05,400 --> 00:13:09,360
Praew, we’re still young.

201
00:13:10,120 --> 00:13:12,560
Why waste time on uncertainty?

202
00:13:26,040 --> 00:13:27,080
Hi, Min.

203
00:13:28,400 --> 00:13:29,600
Why is your phone off?

204
00:13:29,640 --> 00:13:30,920
I couldn’t reach you at all.

205
00:13:31,840 --> 00:13:32,960
My battery died.

206
00:13:33,880 --> 00:13:35,160
Do you have a power bank?

207
00:13:35,320 --> 00:13:36,760
I can buy you one.

208
00:13:37,160 --> 00:13:39,360
It’s okay. I’ll get it myself.

209
00:13:39,840 --> 00:13:41,080
What’s up?

210
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:45,200
I came to take you to eat out
at that place you wanted the other day.

211
00:13:46,400 --> 00:13:47,520
I’m broke.

212
00:13:48,720 --> 00:13:50,040
Let’s go after payday.

213
00:13:50,680 --> 00:13:51,800
It’s on me.

214
00:13:52,200 --> 00:13:54,720
No, I’ll eat with my friend.

215
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:57,760
Hey, do you want Som Tam?

216
00:13:58,000 --> 00:13:58,960
Our usual place?

217
00:13:59,520 --> 00:14:01,520
Familiar taste? Do you want to go?

218
00:14:01,520 --> 00:14:02,160
Of course.

219
00:14:02,600 --> 00:14:03,840
Come eat with me.

220
00:14:04,120 --> 00:14:06,200
You’re my girlfriend.
I can take care of you myself.

221
00:14:06,400 --> 00:14:08,040
Try something new.

222
00:14:08,560 --> 00:14:10,080
You opened my world,

223
00:14:10,920 --> 00:14:12,400
so I’ll open yours.

224
00:14:26,200 --> 00:14:28,760
Didn’t you say you don’t want to be around
that friend who makes you uncomfortable?

225
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:31,560
She just helped with work, nothing more.

226
00:14:32,080 --> 00:14:35,080
And if she likes me, I can’t stop that.

227
00:14:35,760 --> 00:14:37,960
I know you sulked
because I scolded you at the office,

228
00:14:38,840 --> 00:14:40,680
but what you’re doing isn’t right, is it?

229
00:14:41,160 --> 00:14:42,680
I want peace of mind.

230
00:14:43,240 --> 00:14:45,160
Don’t sulk over something like this.

231
00:14:46,480 --> 00:14:51,000
Don’t make me feel guilty
when you can’t give me clarity.

232
00:14:51,400 --> 00:14:52,680
What do you want me to do?

233
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:55,000
Ignore everyone and date you?

234
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:57,480
I’m not alone like you,

235
00:14:58,040 --> 00:14:59,640
who don’t have to care about others.

236
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:10,960
I’m sorry. I didn’t mean it like that.

237
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:16,360
It’s okay. I understand.

238
00:15:16,920 --> 00:15:19,680
But I just want you to know that
I’m not asking for too much.

239
00:15:19,720 --> 00:15:21,720
It’s just what partners normally give.

240
00:15:23,880 --> 00:15:25,560
You want to meet my family, right?

241
00:15:26,280 --> 00:15:28,880
Fine. I’ll take you.

242
00:15:30,600 --> 00:15:32,160
Maybe then you’ll understand me.

243
00:15:34,880 --> 00:15:36,160
Up to you.

244
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:38,960
Think it over.

245
00:15:40,480 --> 00:15:42,880
Maybe you’ll find someone
who understands you better.

246
00:15:43,520 --> 00:15:45,560
Maybe I’m too young for you.

247
00:16:39,480 --> 00:16:41,000
Do you want pineapple? It’ll wake you up.

248
00:16:43,400 --> 00:16:45,520
No, I don’t like sour things.

249
00:16:48,760 --> 00:16:49,480
Okay.

250
00:16:51,960 --> 00:16:54,840
What’s wrong? Why are you so drunk?

251
00:16:57,680 --> 00:17:00,400
Nothing. I drink like this normally.

252
00:17:00,680 --> 00:17:01,920
Do I need a reason?

253
00:17:02,560 --> 00:17:05,000
Fine. You hired me as your manager.

254
00:17:05,319 --> 00:17:06,760
I’m here to take care of you.

255
00:17:06,880 --> 00:17:09,240
I’m not stopping you
from drinking or partying,

256
00:17:09,280 --> 00:17:10,560
but don’t act like this.

257
00:17:11,079 --> 00:17:12,119
It’ll ruin your work.

258
00:17:13,319 --> 00:17:14,839
I showed up anyway, didn’t I?

259
00:17:14,839 --> 00:17:16,160
Stop nagging like a mom.

260
00:17:16,400 --> 00:17:18,040
I hired you as my manager.

261
00:17:18,880 --> 00:17:19,560
Mm.

262
00:17:21,040 --> 00:17:22,359
Then rest for now.

263
00:17:22,640 --> 00:17:24,560
I’ll wake you up when they’re ready.

264
00:17:26,079 --> 00:17:29,480
Here, an eye mask. I made it for you.

265
00:17:36,200 --> 00:17:38,560
Thanks, but no need next time.

266
00:17:39,160 --> 00:17:40,560
Brands already sent me.

267
00:17:41,200 --> 00:17:44,160
Sure. A simple thanks is enough.

268
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:45,240
There is no need to brag.

269
00:17:45,560 --> 00:17:47,640
I know you’re famous.

270
00:17:49,920 --> 00:17:50,760
Gorya.

271
00:17:51,920 --> 00:17:52,760
Yeah?

272
00:17:56,760 --> 00:17:58,560
Don’t come to work tomorrow.

273
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:02,360
You’re not suited to be a manager.

274
00:18:04,440 --> 00:18:05,120
What?

275
00:18:07,360 --> 00:18:08,960
Are you firing me?

276
00:18:11,400 --> 00:18:12,360
What did I do wrong?

277
00:18:16,800 --> 00:18:18,000
Nothing.

278
00:18:18,760 --> 00:18:20,680
We just don’t click.

279
00:18:21,200 --> 00:18:24,240
And I don’t like people
controlling my life.

280
00:18:24,880 --> 00:18:28,440
I’ll go back to clear things up
with Woonsen.

281
00:18:28,680 --> 00:18:30,040
Back to someone who scams you?

282
00:18:30,920 --> 00:18:32,440
Are you crazy? What are you thinking?

283
00:18:35,560 --> 00:18:37,840
It’s my money, my business.

284
00:18:39,840 --> 00:18:44,680
Yeah, you were the one
who kept begging me to join you,

285
00:18:45,280 --> 00:18:46,560
and now you’re firing me?

286
00:18:47,280 --> 00:18:48,360
Are you insane?

287
00:18:51,880 --> 00:18:53,760
I’ve always been like this.

288
00:18:54,080 --> 00:18:56,520
No one ever told you to fix your attitude?

289
00:18:58,320 --> 00:18:59,280
Fine, I’ll leave.

290
00:19:00,120 --> 00:19:01,560
I didn’t even want this job anyway.

291
00:19:03,560 --> 00:19:05,000
It’s this kind of attitude

292
00:19:06,560 --> 00:19:07,960
that makes you have no friends.

293
00:20:00,040 --> 00:20:03,960
Sha, you haven’t been here in a while.

294
00:20:04,400 --> 00:20:06,080
There are way more
good-looking people now.

295
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:09,760
Really? It feels the same.

296
00:20:09,760 --> 00:20:11,000
No one’s interesting.

297
00:20:28,240 --> 00:20:29,160
Are you sure?

298
00:20:30,080 --> 00:20:31,160
What about that girl?

299
00:20:32,640 --> 00:20:33,760
Did you break up?

300
00:20:35,680 --> 00:20:37,760
Break up? We were never together.

301
00:20:39,120 --> 00:20:40,760
But you like her, don't you?

302
00:20:42,480 --> 00:20:43,920
I’m your ex.

303
00:20:44,600 --> 00:20:46,480
I can tell just by looking into your eyes.

304
00:20:47,080 --> 00:20:48,280
Don’t lie.

305
00:20:51,360 --> 00:20:52,880
It was just a fleeting feeling.

306
00:20:53,120 --> 00:20:54,480
I’m over it now.

307
00:20:56,800 --> 00:20:59,600
You get bored so easily as always.

308
00:21:01,360 --> 00:21:03,000
Win them over, then throw them away.

309
00:21:09,800 --> 00:21:12,760
So if you don’t like her,

310
00:21:15,280 --> 00:21:16,360
can I go after her?

311
00:21:23,560 --> 00:21:26,360
Why did you ask me? Go ask her yourself.

312
00:21:29,800 --> 00:21:31,000
I’m just being respectful.

313
00:21:34,600 --> 00:21:36,160
But if you’re not into her,

314
00:21:38,480 --> 00:21:39,680
I’m going for it.

315
00:22:21,640 --> 00:22:23,560
Dating a puppy girl is like this.

316
00:22:24,160 --> 00:22:25,280
You have to adjust a lot.

317
00:22:26,240 --> 00:22:27,880
These days it’s not about age.

318
00:22:28,120 --> 00:22:29,480
It’s about attitude.

319
00:22:31,880 --> 00:22:34,320
Have some sympathy for her.

320
00:22:34,360 --> 00:22:36,080
If I were her, I’d feel insecure too.

321
00:22:36,200 --> 00:22:37,640
Dating you is like dating a ghost.

322
00:22:37,680 --> 00:22:38,880
No presence at all.

323
00:22:39,480 --> 00:22:42,200
Not everyone shows off their relationship
like you do.

324
00:22:42,480 --> 00:22:43,560
So where is she today?

325
00:22:43,760 --> 00:22:46,680
Not clinging to you
on the dance floor anymore?

326
00:22:46,880 --> 00:22:48,680
She said she wants a break from partying.

327
00:22:48,720 --> 00:22:50,040
She wants to focus on work.

328
00:22:56,320 --> 00:22:57,360
Prim, Min.

329
00:22:58,200 --> 00:22:59,000
Oh, Oil?

330
00:22:59,000 --> 00:23:00,360
-Hello.
-Hi.

331
00:23:00,400 --> 00:23:02,040
I didn’t expect to see you here.

332
00:23:02,040 --> 00:23:03,640
We usually only meet in meeting rooms.

333
00:23:03,880 --> 00:23:06,680
Let me take a break from work for once.
I just want to let loose.

334
00:23:06,880 --> 00:23:09,840
But I never thought I’d run into
a Ladybird duo here.

335
00:23:10,000 --> 00:23:12,120
With Prim, I’m not that surprised.

336
00:23:12,160 --> 00:23:13,320
But Min too?

337
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:15,120
You’re into this scene too?

338
00:23:15,560 --> 00:23:17,960
My friend just turned pro.

339
00:23:18,120 --> 00:23:19,240
Prim!

340
00:23:19,560 --> 00:23:20,440
Sorry?

341
00:23:21,400 --> 00:23:24,040
She’s just joking. Don’t listen to her.

342
00:23:25,120 --> 00:23:28,680
I don’t really want to talk
about work here, but I have a new client.

343
00:23:28,920 --> 00:23:30,360
It might suit…

344
00:23:30,480 --> 00:23:31,360
Sorry.

345
00:23:31,920 --> 00:23:35,080
It might suit Ladybird.
It’s a spa product.

346
00:23:35,760 --> 00:23:38,040
So I thought
you might want to try it together.

347
00:23:44,760 --> 00:23:46,000
Try what?

348
00:23:46,880 --> 00:23:47,960
Try the spa.

349
00:23:47,960 --> 00:23:49,760
Oh.

350
00:23:50,000 --> 00:23:51,920
Sure, I’ll contact you later.

351
00:23:52,120 --> 00:23:54,520
Thank you for always bringing us work.

352
00:23:55,480 --> 00:23:56,400
No problem.

353
00:23:56,600 --> 00:23:58,960
I like people
who are beautiful and talented.

354
00:24:01,240 --> 00:24:02,280
I’ll get going then.

355
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:10,120
I think she likes you.

356
00:24:10,440 --> 00:24:11,160
Huh?

357
00:24:11,360 --> 00:24:12,160
Seriously.

358
00:24:13,400 --> 00:24:15,080
I’m going to the restroom. I need to pee.

359
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:20,280
What did I do wrong?

360
00:24:20,840 --> 00:24:21,880
Tell me.

361
00:24:22,320 --> 00:24:24,360
If I did something wrong, just say it.

362
00:24:26,640 --> 00:24:28,360
Do you have someone new already?

363
00:24:30,360 --> 00:24:31,360
Tell me.

364
00:24:32,280 --> 00:24:34,280
Don’t hang up. Let’s talk first!

365
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:50,440
Oh, Airy?

366
00:24:50,920 --> 00:24:51,800
Prim.

367
00:24:53,520 --> 00:24:54,560
Is something wrong?

368
00:24:57,400 --> 00:24:59,080
I had a fight with my partner.

369
00:25:02,440 --> 00:25:04,560
Out of nowhere, she broke up with me.

370
00:25:06,720 --> 00:25:08,960
She didn’t even give me a reason.

371
00:25:11,680 --> 00:25:15,240
I was going to meet her here to talk,
but she didn’t come.

372
00:25:17,160 --> 00:25:18,680
It’s my birthday today too.

373
00:25:19,640 --> 00:25:23,160
Oh, that’s awful.

374
00:25:23,760 --> 00:25:24,960
Did you come alone?

375
00:25:26,320 --> 00:25:27,240
Yes.

376
00:25:29,120 --> 00:25:30,960
I don’t dare go outside.

377
00:25:31,240 --> 00:25:32,160
I feel embarrassed.

378
00:25:32,200 --> 00:25:33,560
Hey, it’s okay.

379
00:25:34,360 --> 00:25:36,160
Come hang out with me and Min.

380
00:25:38,880 --> 00:25:40,160
Are you sure?

381
00:25:41,000 --> 00:25:43,760
You guys came to have fun.

382
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:45,960
I don’t want to make things awkward.

383
00:25:46,320 --> 00:25:48,120
Hey, we work together.

384
00:25:48,160 --> 00:25:50,480
We’re like sisters,
so we should take care of each other.

385
00:25:54,240 --> 00:25:55,760
If you need help,

386
00:25:56,080 --> 00:25:59,240
with work or personal stuff, just tell me.

387
00:25:59,280 --> 00:26:00,840
I’ll help if I can.

388
00:26:03,840 --> 00:26:05,960
Can I hug you?

389
00:26:07,760 --> 00:26:10,160
I really need someone right now.

390
00:26:13,680 --> 00:26:14,560
It’s okay.

391
00:26:33,920 --> 00:26:38,360
♪ It’s rare to feel this way,
can’t catch my breath ♪

392
00:26:38,640 --> 00:26:41,880
♪ Got this feeling,
my heart’s such a mess, a mess ♪

393
00:26:41,920 --> 00:26:44,040
TEXT ME WITH YOU GET HOME

394
00:26:44,080 --> 00:26:47,320
♪ Just a look in your eyes
stirs up a storm inside, why? ♪

395
00:26:47,360 --> 00:26:48,480
♪ Cause of you ♪

396
00:26:48,520 --> 00:26:49,720
♪ What you do ♪

397
00:26:49,720 --> 00:26:52,680
♪ You’ve got me melting, can’t lie ♪

398
00:26:53,160 --> 00:26:56,040
Can we hear some cheers
for my MV heroine?

399
00:27:06,920 --> 00:27:10,480
♪ Letting you walk away?
That’s something I won’t do ♪

400
00:27:10,760 --> 00:27:14,800
♪ Would you mind if I fell for you? ♪

401
00:27:14,960 --> 00:27:17,360
♪ There’s no one next to you? ♪

402
00:27:17,640 --> 00:27:20,280
♪ You’re making me breathless, baby ♪

403
00:27:20,320 --> 00:27:23,960
♪ Would you mind if I start right now? ♪

404
00:27:24,560 --> 00:27:26,760
♪ Hope you will allow ♪

405
00:27:27,800 --> 00:27:32,480
♪ Want to win your heart
before someone else steals you away ♪

406
00:28:07,400 --> 00:28:08,840
Oh wow, look at you.

407
00:28:12,600 --> 00:28:14,680
Sha, get up.

408
00:28:14,880 --> 00:28:16,040
We’re closed. Come on.

409
00:28:16,760 --> 00:28:17,960
Are you okay?

410
00:28:18,120 --> 00:28:18,840
Get up.

411
00:28:19,320 --> 00:28:20,200
Hurry up. Go home.

412
00:28:20,200 --> 00:28:21,240
I’ll call a car for you.

413
00:28:21,920 --> 00:28:24,280
No, I’m not drunk yet.

414
00:28:24,880 --> 00:28:26,680
Hey, can I get more wine?

415
00:28:27,320 --> 00:28:30,640
You’re way past drunk.

416
00:28:31,040 --> 00:28:32,280
Come on, let’s go home.

417
00:28:34,120 --> 00:28:35,160
Where’s Gorya?

418
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:36,560
Why isn’t she taking care of you?

419
00:28:36,680 --> 00:28:37,960
Isn’t she your manager?

420
00:28:38,360 --> 00:28:40,760
She’s not anymore. Just let her go.

421
00:28:41,160 --> 00:28:43,120
Eh? What are you talking about?

422
00:28:44,640 --> 00:28:46,680
So what now?
Should I take you back to your condo?

423
00:28:48,480 --> 00:28:51,760
Whatever. I live alone anyway.

424
00:29:12,040 --> 00:29:14,280
Oh, Airy. How are you?

425
00:29:14,960 --> 00:29:17,480
I’m still hungover, but I’m okay.

426
00:29:18,160 --> 00:29:19,840
Honestly, you could take the day off.

427
00:29:19,880 --> 00:29:21,240
There’s nothing urgent today.

428
00:29:21,560 --> 00:29:23,320
We can work from home.

429
00:29:23,880 --> 00:29:24,840
It’s okay.

430
00:29:25,080 --> 00:29:26,880
It’s better to come out and work.

431
00:29:27,080 --> 00:29:28,440
Staying home makes me sad.

432
00:29:29,520 --> 00:29:31,960
If you’re sad, just let it out.

433
00:29:32,840 --> 00:29:35,080
Give yourself time,
and then pull yourself together.

434
00:29:35,120 --> 00:29:37,120
If you bottle it up, it’ll explode.

435
00:29:38,240 --> 00:29:41,480
Bambi is so lucky
to date someone like you.

436
00:29:41,720 --> 00:29:42,640
Oh please,

437
00:29:43,560 --> 00:29:46,240
sometimes I’m a pain in the ass too.

438
00:29:46,560 --> 00:29:47,960
No one’s perfect.

439
00:29:48,800 --> 00:29:52,880
But I think you’re the kind of partner
many people would want.

440
00:30:07,840 --> 00:30:11,480
Ugh, I’m still hungover,

441
00:30:12,000 --> 00:30:13,600
and I have to submit the draft tomorrow.

442
00:30:13,960 --> 00:30:15,680
Should I go make you some coffee?

443
00:30:15,880 --> 00:30:16,880
It might help you wake up.

444
00:30:22,120 --> 00:30:23,640
Yeah, that sounds good.

445
00:30:24,600 --> 00:30:25,360
Sure.

446
00:30:51,640 --> 00:30:53,080
If you’re making coffee for Prim,

447
00:30:53,480 --> 00:30:55,160
she doesn’t take sugar.

448
00:30:56,480 --> 00:30:57,760
She’s hungover,

449
00:30:58,320 --> 00:30:59,960
so she asked me to make it for her.

450
00:31:02,080 --> 00:31:06,280
I didn’t know an AE
had to make coffee for the company owner.

451
00:31:06,960 --> 00:31:08,680
It wasn’t in the job description.

452
00:31:09,080 --> 00:31:10,160
You’re very eager.

453
00:31:11,440 --> 00:31:12,840
I like taking care of people.

454
00:31:14,280 --> 00:31:16,280
I want to take care of Prim.

455
00:31:18,680 --> 00:31:20,960
Why don’t you leave that to me,
her girlfriend?

456
00:31:21,920 --> 00:31:23,480
You have your own partner too.

457
00:31:24,320 --> 00:31:27,160
Do you like seeing others take your place?

458
00:31:27,720 --> 00:31:28,560
We broke up.

459
00:31:29,800 --> 00:31:30,960
Oh, you broke up.

460
00:31:31,520 --> 00:31:33,360
So you’re rushing to find someone new?

461
00:31:33,960 --> 00:31:36,160
Maybe you should find someone
who isn’t taken.

462
00:31:44,440 --> 00:31:46,440
I admire your effort,

463
00:31:47,960 --> 00:31:49,480
but you need to tell the difference

464
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:52,560
between someone liking you
and simple kindness.

465
00:32:02,720 --> 00:32:04,080
Last night was fun though.

466
00:32:05,200 --> 00:32:06,720
Aren’t you overthinking it?

467
00:32:07,160 --> 00:32:10,560
Being this jealous,
Prim might feel uncomfortable.

468
00:32:14,000 --> 00:32:18,360
Jealousy makes our relationship stronger.

469
00:32:19,600 --> 00:32:20,880
Then that’s good.

470
00:32:21,080 --> 00:32:22,440
No need to be afraid of me.

471
00:32:22,560 --> 00:32:23,760
I’m just friendly.

472
00:32:25,960 --> 00:32:27,080
I’m not afraid.

473
00:32:27,880 --> 00:32:29,080
I’m just annoyed.

474
00:32:30,600 --> 00:32:33,560
Save your friendliness for dogs and cats,

475
00:32:34,440 --> 00:32:35,840
not someone else’s partner.

476
00:33:20,480 --> 00:33:21,120
Sis!

477
00:33:21,440 --> 00:33:23,640
Ant, wake up already!

478
00:33:24,840 --> 00:33:26,560
How did I end up sleeping here with you?

479
00:33:36,600 --> 00:33:37,880
You were really drunk,

480
00:33:39,160 --> 00:33:41,280
and last night we…

481
00:33:49,240 --> 00:33:50,480
Nothing happened.

482
00:33:50,880 --> 00:33:52,160
I’m just messing with you.

483
00:33:52,320 --> 00:33:53,960
Oh my gosh, you scared me!

484
00:33:54,120 --> 00:33:56,880
You were wasted,
so I dragged you here to my hostel.

485
00:33:58,000 --> 00:34:00,320
You kept talking about your manager
all night,

486
00:34:00,440 --> 00:34:02,600
crying while telling the story,
and then you fell asleep.

487
00:34:05,240 --> 00:34:06,680
That really scared me.

488
00:34:08,480 --> 00:34:09,679
I have a partner, you know.

489
00:34:10,080 --> 00:34:13,560
Even if you’re Miss Universe-level pretty,
my partner’s still prettier.

490
00:34:15,960 --> 00:34:17,560
Anyway, thank you.

491
00:34:18,520 --> 00:34:19,840
I’m a total mess right now.

492
00:34:20,560 --> 00:34:22,960
This is such a big deal.
How did you keep it to yourself?

493
00:34:25,400 --> 00:34:27,159
Who could I even turn to?

494
00:34:27,360 --> 00:34:30,280
My mom’s abroad,
and I barely have any friends.

495
00:34:42,400 --> 00:34:43,639
Did you forget about me?

496
00:34:50,520 --> 00:34:52,159
Here, drink this.
It’ll help your hangover.

497
00:34:53,040 --> 00:34:53,880
Thank you.

498
00:34:55,239 --> 00:35:00,640
If Ant hadn’t told me
about that bitch Woonsen,

499
00:35:01,080 --> 00:35:03,160
you wouldn’t have told me, right?

500
00:35:06,840 --> 00:35:08,720
I didn’t want to drag you into it.

501
00:35:10,360 --> 00:35:11,600
So you fired me

502
00:35:12,720 --> 00:35:14,880
and let her blackmail you instead?

503
00:35:16,160 --> 00:35:17,040
Are you crazy?

504
00:35:18,480 --> 00:35:19,840
Don’t give in.

505
00:35:21,800 --> 00:35:23,480
If that video gets leaked,

506
00:35:24,440 --> 00:35:26,040
I’m the one who’ll be ruined.

507
00:35:26,440 --> 00:35:31,560
People will say I got famous
by selling myself.

508
00:35:33,160 --> 00:35:42,440
Shasha, you know
you earned everything yourself.

509
00:35:49,840 --> 00:35:51,480
Don’t let yourself become a victim.

510
00:35:55,400 --> 00:35:56,640
I’ll help you.

511
00:36:08,800 --> 00:36:09,960
Cry it all out.

512
00:36:13,040 --> 00:36:14,880
Be weak just for today.

513
00:36:18,400 --> 00:36:19,960
I’m sorry for firing you.

514
00:36:24,000 --> 00:36:26,760
It’s okay. I understand.

515
00:36:27,920 --> 00:36:29,160
Don’t overthink it.

516
00:36:31,040 --> 00:36:33,880
We can’t change the past,

517
00:36:35,960 --> 00:36:37,560
but we can fight it.

518
00:36:42,320 --> 00:36:44,680
Don’t let bad people
have a place in this world.

519
00:36:45,880 --> 00:36:47,760
Everyone’s ready to help you.

520
00:36:49,400 --> 00:36:50,760
You just have to speak up.

521
00:36:52,640 --> 00:36:54,240
You’re not alone.

522
00:37:08,400 --> 00:37:09,240
Thank you.

523
00:37:31,320 --> 00:37:33,240
Are you sure you left it in my room?

524
00:37:35,360 --> 00:37:38,000
I’ve searched my room and faculty,
but I still can’t find it.

525
00:37:40,720 --> 00:37:42,120
Did you check your old place?

526
00:37:42,160 --> 00:37:43,480
Did you ask Boom?

527
00:37:46,160 --> 00:37:49,040
I haven’t been back since I moved out.

528
00:37:57,920 --> 00:37:58,760
It’s here.

529
00:38:02,960 --> 00:38:04,360
Thank you, Min.

530
00:38:05,320 --> 00:38:06,560
I’ll get going.

531
00:38:12,000 --> 00:38:13,600
So this is how you want to play it?

532
00:38:14,120 --> 00:38:16,600
Play what? I just came to get my stuff.

533
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:18,760
I’m talking about you doing it out of spite.

534
00:38:19,320 --> 00:38:21,560
Going back to hang out with the friend
who likes you?

535
00:38:23,600 --> 00:38:24,960
I’m not doing it out of spite.

536
00:38:25,800 --> 00:38:27,360
I just think

537
00:38:27,360 --> 00:38:31,160
being with people in the same circle
might be more enjoyable.

538
00:38:32,280 --> 00:38:37,760
Also, I don’t want to feel invisible,
like I have no status.

539
00:38:38,440 --> 00:38:42,160
You already know the condition.

540
00:38:44,360 --> 00:38:47,520
I do, but I still feel hurt.

541
00:38:48,280 --> 00:38:49,600
It’s okay to feel that way,

542
00:38:50,760 --> 00:38:52,520
but don’t hurt my feelings.

543
00:38:52,920 --> 00:38:53,920
I don’t like that.

544
00:38:55,800 --> 00:38:57,880
Everyone has their own timing, right?

545
00:39:14,520 --> 00:39:17,880
Well, it’s not that
I don’t want to go public with you.

546
00:39:20,920 --> 00:39:23,160
I really want to tell everyone
we’re together.

547
00:39:24,600 --> 00:39:27,280
Why wouldn’t I want to hold your hand,
show you off,

548
00:39:27,960 --> 00:39:30,400
post pictures,
and show the world we’re a couple?

549
00:39:36,800 --> 00:39:37,760
How about this?

550
00:39:40,640 --> 00:39:42,200
I’ll take you to meet my family.

551
00:39:45,280 --> 00:39:47,160
But we have to take it step by step.

552
00:39:48,680 --> 00:39:50,680
My family isn’t open-minded enough yet.

553
00:39:53,400 --> 00:39:56,200
I still can’t tell them
I’m dating a woman.

554
00:39:59,560 --> 00:40:01,160
This is as much as I can do for now.

555
00:40:01,400 --> 00:40:02,560
Are you okay with that?

556
00:40:13,320 --> 00:40:17,360
Why wouldn’t I want to show people
how adorable my girlfriend is?

557
00:40:20,640 --> 00:40:21,360
Okay.

558
00:40:22,440 --> 00:40:24,280
We can take it slow and learn together.

559
00:40:28,160 --> 00:40:29,520
Then…

560
00:40:32,280 --> 00:40:33,840
stay over tonight?

561
00:40:51,160 --> 00:40:52,640
Of course I’m staying.

562
00:40:54,000 --> 00:40:55,360
I’ve missed you like crazy.

563
00:41:40,120 --> 00:41:43,120
You’ve been staying at my place this long.
Doesn’t your mom mind?

564
00:41:44,440 --> 00:41:46,440
I’m thinking of…

565
00:41:48,040 --> 00:41:49,280
moving in with you.

566
00:41:50,000 --> 00:41:51,880
What? I didn’t even invite you.

567
00:41:51,920 --> 00:41:53,160
You invited yourself.

568
00:41:54,440 --> 00:41:57,480
Why? You don’t want me around anymore?

569
00:41:57,920 --> 00:41:59,560
Planning to bring someone else over?

570
00:41:59,600 --> 00:42:01,240
Do you want me to schedule it for you?

571
00:42:01,320 --> 00:42:03,080
What? No.

572
00:42:04,880 --> 00:42:08,840
Besides Gorya, who I almost hooked up with
before you interrupted,

573
00:42:10,280 --> 00:42:12,160
I haven’t brought anyone else here.

574
00:42:18,680 --> 00:42:22,680
What about Airy?

575
00:42:22,960 --> 00:42:26,840
Bambi, she just started recently.

576
00:42:27,080 --> 00:42:28,040
Are you jealous already?

577
00:42:28,080 --> 00:42:30,360
I don’t know. I just don’t like her face.

578
00:42:30,400 --> 00:42:31,960
Something feels off about her.

579
00:42:32,040 --> 00:42:33,480
She seems intense.

580
00:42:33,760 --> 00:42:38,480
She’s trying to dress like me,
like she wants to be your type.

581
00:42:39,280 --> 00:42:41,360
My type? What’s that?

582
00:42:42,000 --> 00:42:46,400
Petite, long hair.
That’s your type, like me and Gorya.

583
00:42:47,160 --> 00:42:49,760
Come on, I told you Gorya’s just a junior.

584
00:42:50,720 --> 00:42:54,480
And my type isn’t just about looks.

585
00:42:55,160 --> 00:42:57,360
I like you for being you.

586
00:42:58,400 --> 00:42:59,640
You’re different.

587
00:43:01,200 --> 00:43:04,600
No one in Thailand compares to you,
I’m telling you.

588
00:43:05,080 --> 00:43:07,680
Not just Thailand but the whole world.

589
00:43:12,160 --> 00:43:13,960
Come on, stop.

590
00:43:15,640 --> 00:43:17,080
Just be nice to her.

591
00:43:17,120 --> 00:43:20,480
I have to work with her
and you have to meet her again.

592
00:43:20,880 --> 00:43:21,400
Fine.

593
00:43:21,440 --> 00:43:24,560
Just work, and nothing else.

594
00:43:25,320 --> 00:43:26,720
Nothing else? Like what?

595
00:43:27,920 --> 00:43:28,840
I don’t know.

596
00:43:29,760 --> 00:43:31,480
If she comes to your room,

597
00:43:32,000 --> 00:43:33,760
she’ll meet the real Bambi!

598
00:43:34,840 --> 00:43:38,160
Sure, I’m scared.

599
00:43:38,840 --> 00:43:40,360
There’s nothing going on.

600
00:43:40,680 --> 00:43:41,760
Just so you know.

601
00:43:42,280 --> 00:43:46,320
No one gets close to me like you do.

602
00:43:47,120 --> 00:43:51,040
We’ll see about that.

603
00:43:53,400 --> 00:43:55,440
Here, a little extra love.

604
00:44:01,200 --> 00:44:02,800
Grandma, it's delicious.

605
00:44:02,840 --> 00:44:04,240
Delicious.

606
00:44:05,880 --> 00:44:07,000
This one’s good.

607
00:44:07,040 --> 00:44:08,040
Delicious.

608
00:44:10,360 --> 00:44:11,960
Are you Min’s colleague?

609
00:44:14,680 --> 00:44:15,560
Yes.

610
00:44:16,000 --> 00:44:18,320
She’s a regular freelance photographer
at the office.

611
00:44:18,360 --> 00:44:19,640
She takes really beautiful photos.

612
00:44:21,400 --> 00:44:23,680
What about your parents?
Where are they from?

613
00:44:24,280 --> 00:44:25,240
What do they do?

614
00:44:28,800 --> 00:44:30,480
My parents passed away when I was young.

615
00:44:31,120 --> 00:44:32,880
It’s just me and my older sister now,

616
00:44:33,280 --> 00:44:36,480
but she’s married, so I live alone.

617
00:44:45,520 --> 00:44:46,920
Are you a tomboy?

618
00:44:53,360 --> 00:44:54,520
I like women,

619
00:44:55,480 --> 00:44:57,480
but you can call it whatever you want.

620
00:45:06,520 --> 00:45:07,800
Your mom told me already.

621
00:45:10,160 --> 00:45:11,440
Did you break up with Park?

622
00:45:13,600 --> 00:45:14,720
Why did you break up?

623
00:45:15,240 --> 00:45:16,240
I like him.

624
00:45:16,680 --> 00:45:18,960
You dated for years. What a waste.

625
00:45:20,680 --> 00:45:22,440
What did you do to him?

626
00:45:24,080 --> 00:45:26,480
Why do you assume I did something?

627
00:45:26,600 --> 00:45:28,320
Why don’t you think he might be a jerk?

628
00:45:28,800 --> 00:45:31,960
If people love each other,
they should be able to endure things.

629
00:45:33,200 --> 00:45:35,640
Endure him hurting me,
both physically and mentally?

630
00:45:37,120 --> 00:45:38,000
Come on.

631
00:45:38,240 --> 00:45:39,760
Why are we talking about
something so stressful?

632
00:45:39,800 --> 00:45:41,440
Our daughter rarely comes home.

633
00:45:42,640 --> 00:45:43,760
Eat, eat.

634
00:45:45,040 --> 00:45:45,840
Praew, eat.

635
00:45:48,440 --> 00:45:50,280
Here, have some duck.

636
00:45:50,320 --> 00:45:51,000
Here you are.

637
00:45:51,960 --> 00:45:52,840
A big piece.

638
00:45:55,640 --> 00:45:58,280
It looks like this family won’t have anyone
to carry on the family line.

639
00:46:03,920 --> 00:46:07,560
You should hurry and find a boyfriend
and get married soon.

640
00:46:08,360 --> 00:46:09,720
Don’t end up like Auntie Ju.

641
00:46:09,720 --> 00:46:13,600
See? She has no family, no one,
growing old alone.

642
00:46:15,560 --> 00:46:18,560
Why? She seems happy.

643
00:46:18,720 --> 00:46:19,680
She has plenty of money.

644
00:46:19,960 --> 00:46:20,760
Come on.

645
00:46:21,200 --> 00:46:23,280
Money isn’t as important as family.

646
00:46:23,640 --> 00:46:24,840
I think it is.

647
00:46:26,000 --> 00:46:28,160
You both even borrowed money from her.

648
00:46:34,720 --> 00:46:36,160
Let’s just eat.

649
00:46:37,040 --> 00:46:37,840
Eat, eat.

650
00:46:38,560 --> 00:46:40,880
Grandma, it’s delicious.

651
00:46:41,320 --> 00:46:43,600
Eat a lot.

652
00:46:47,160 --> 00:46:50,040
Okay, I’ll check everything.
Then go get Shasha.

653
00:46:50,280 --> 00:46:51,360
Got it, Gorya.

654
00:46:51,840 --> 00:46:53,680
Are you okay?

655
00:46:54,520 --> 00:46:56,200
There’s no problem between you two, right?

656
00:46:57,600 --> 00:47:02,160
Prim told me
you used to have issues with Shasha.

657
00:47:03,680 --> 00:47:04,760
It’s nothing now.

658
00:47:05,040 --> 00:47:07,080
I was just a junior who admired her.

659
00:47:07,320 --> 00:47:08,880
That sounds familiar.

660
00:47:09,920 --> 00:47:11,360
Alright, go ahead. Take care of it for me.

661
00:47:11,400 --> 00:47:12,080
Sure.

662
00:47:20,520 --> 00:47:21,760
Need any help?

663
00:47:22,840 --> 00:47:25,280
No, I’ve got everything handled.

664
00:47:27,920 --> 00:47:29,760
Shasha’s my friend too.

665
00:47:30,200 --> 00:47:31,480
Let me help.

666
00:47:32,040 --> 00:47:33,240
I bought lots of snacks.

667
00:47:33,480 --> 00:47:35,040
Let me set them up for the press.

668
00:48:31,880 --> 00:48:33,000
Ready, Shasha?

669
00:48:33,040 --> 00:48:34,680
Min has arranged the press already.

670
00:48:35,680 --> 00:48:37,240
Even if I’m not ready, I have to be.

671
00:48:38,360 --> 00:48:40,440
I don’t know if I can control my emotions.

672
00:48:40,560 --> 00:48:42,680
I’m afraid I’ll cry
and won’t be able to speak.

673
00:48:45,760 --> 00:48:50,680
But thank you all so much for helping me.

674
00:48:51,680 --> 00:48:52,560
It’s okay.

675
00:48:55,760 --> 00:48:59,480
I know it’s hard to talk about something
you want to forget.

676
00:49:02,520 --> 00:49:05,640
But just deciding to do this
is already so brave,

677
00:49:06,320 --> 00:49:09,720
and it’ll help other women
going through this too.

678
00:49:11,520 --> 00:49:12,840
Remember,

679
00:49:14,520 --> 00:49:19,080
you didn’t get into this industry
because of that jerk or Woonsen.

680
00:49:20,080 --> 00:49:25,280
You got here because
you’re beautiful, talented,

681
00:49:26,400 --> 00:49:27,760
and you do it well.

682
00:49:32,520 --> 00:49:34,160
Hey, don’t cry yet.

683
00:49:34,240 --> 00:49:36,160
You won’t look good on camera
for the interview.

684
00:49:37,240 --> 00:49:39,240
Okay, I won’t cry.

685
00:49:41,600 --> 00:49:43,160
Just talk as much as you can.

686
00:49:43,480 --> 00:49:45,560
If it’s too much, signal us right away.

687
00:49:45,920 --> 00:49:46,960
Thank you so much.

688
00:49:47,680 --> 00:49:48,840
Remember,

689
00:49:49,760 --> 00:49:51,600
you’re not going through this alone.

690
00:49:52,160 --> 00:49:56,560
You have us, Min, everyone at Ladybird,

691
00:49:57,680 --> 00:49:58,760
and Gorya too.

692
00:50:02,320 --> 00:50:04,480
We’re all ready to support you.

693
00:50:14,960 --> 00:50:16,080
It’s time, Prim.

694
00:50:16,160 --> 00:50:17,280
The reporters are here.

695
00:50:36,440 --> 00:50:38,560
When did you start working
with your sister?

696
00:50:40,280 --> 00:50:42,160
Not long ago. I just started.

697
00:50:48,040 --> 00:50:49,760
I’m rooting for you today.

698
00:50:50,800 --> 00:50:54,760
I’m sorry if I ever made you feel bad.

699
00:50:57,160 --> 00:51:00,760
Looking back, it was all in my head.

700
00:51:03,520 --> 00:51:04,760
No need to apologize.

701
00:51:05,160 --> 00:51:06,960
I had my faults too.

702
00:51:09,440 --> 00:51:10,880
If you have a partner,

703
00:51:11,480 --> 00:51:13,560
don’t go around being nice to other girls.

704
00:51:14,160 --> 00:51:16,760
Actually, don’t even smile.

705
00:51:17,360 --> 00:51:20,320
Your smile alone could make
hundreds of girls fall for you.

706
00:51:24,560 --> 00:51:27,480
Anyway, I hope everything
goes smoothly today.

707
00:51:28,720 --> 00:51:30,160
I’m always cheering for you.

708
00:51:31,280 --> 00:51:32,160
Thank you.

709
00:52:02,960 --> 00:52:05,560
Hello, I’m Shasha.

710
00:52:06,120 --> 00:52:08,040
Thank you everyone for coming today.

711
00:52:09,000 --> 00:52:12,840
As you know,
I’ve had issues with my former manager.

712
00:52:13,440 --> 00:52:17,560
She is attempting to blackmail me,
using things from my past.

713
00:52:18,880 --> 00:52:24,840
What you may hear are things
I can’t go back and change.

714
00:52:25,200 --> 00:52:27,960
But I will move forward.

715
00:52:28,280 --> 00:52:31,440
I won’t let anyone discredit my efforts.

716
00:52:31,840 --> 00:52:38,400
And I want anyone who has been harrassed
to speak up about it.

717
00:52:50,480 --> 00:52:53,560
I’m ready to support you
and be there for you.

718
00:52:53,840 --> 00:52:56,280
Let’s not let this happen to anyone else.

719
00:54:10,640 --> 00:54:11,880
Are you Ms. Woonsen?

720
00:54:12,800 --> 00:54:14,520
The court has issued a warrant
for your arrest

721
00:54:14,520 --> 00:54:18,480
on charges of fraud and intimidation.

722
00:54:18,720 --> 00:54:20,560
Please come with us
to the station for questioning.

723
00:54:26,040 --> 00:54:29,640
Thank you so much
for leading the press conference today.

724
00:54:30,320 --> 00:54:32,520
No problem. I’m into this stuff.

725
00:54:32,800 --> 00:54:36,840
We’re women. Why the hell
hurt each other instead of helping?

726
00:54:38,600 --> 00:54:40,120
Alright, I can tell you’re really into it.

727
00:54:40,160 --> 00:54:41,400
Girl power.

728
00:54:41,960 --> 00:54:43,520
Just talking about it gets me worked up.

729
00:54:46,720 --> 00:54:48,200
Careful, you’ll get drunk.

730
00:54:48,720 --> 00:54:49,640
What’s there to be afraid of?

731
00:54:49,680 --> 00:54:52,160
It’s my place. If I’m drunk, I’ll just sleep.

732
00:55:37,680 --> 00:55:38,360
Here you are.

733
00:55:39,360 --> 00:55:41,640
The tee you wanted is finished.

734
00:55:42,680 --> 00:55:45,680
Thank you. How much? I’ll help pay.

735
00:55:45,960 --> 00:55:47,560
No need to act rich.

736
00:55:47,760 --> 00:55:51,120
Just wear it. Others will want it too.

737
00:55:52,440 --> 00:55:55,680
Oh, I see. So I’m your presenter?

738
00:55:56,560 --> 00:55:59,120
Watch, it’ll be sold out in 10 minutes.

739
00:56:00,120 --> 00:56:01,600
I’ll get ready to pin the product.

740
00:56:11,600 --> 00:56:13,080
You’ve been drinking.

741
00:56:13,600 --> 00:56:14,840
How will you drive home?

742
00:56:16,200 --> 00:56:18,360
I’ll call someone to drive for me.

743
00:56:27,000 --> 00:56:28,280
You can sleep here.

744
00:56:30,040 --> 00:56:31,520
You’ve got clothes to change into.

745
00:56:34,280 --> 00:56:37,080
Now you’re the one
inviting me to stay over?

746
00:56:38,520 --> 00:56:39,880
No need to pretend.

747
00:57:04,320 --> 00:57:08,080
Honestly, I do want to sleep over
but maybe another time.

748
00:57:09,200 --> 00:57:11,440
I want today to end like this.

749
00:57:12,640 --> 00:57:13,960
It feels just right.

750
00:57:15,240 --> 00:57:20,040
Sometimes drinking beer
and having a good conversation

751
00:57:20,640 --> 00:57:22,160
is better than sex.

752
00:57:27,400 --> 00:57:28,640
I’ll head home now.

753
00:57:29,280 --> 00:57:30,840
Thanks for the tee.

754
00:57:58,600 --> 00:58:01,080
Are you saying I’m not allowed to have
any lesbian friends other than Prim?

755
00:58:01,120 --> 00:58:03,680
But that’s just how this community is.

756
00:58:03,840 --> 00:58:06,240
When someone new comes along,
people want them.

757
00:58:06,480 --> 00:58:07,600
I’m sorry.

758
00:58:07,640 --> 00:58:10,440
I didn’t think
it would make you two fight.

759
00:58:10,600 --> 00:58:13,320
She’s so two-faced!
You still believe her?!

760
00:58:13,560 --> 00:58:15,680
What do I have to do
to make you my stylist exclusively?

761
00:58:15,880 --> 00:58:19,320
Being in a position
where you get to choose, it’s kind of fun.

762
00:58:19,480 --> 00:58:21,520
You can’t handle everything on your own.

763
00:58:21,560 --> 00:58:23,800
You’ve still got me,
and we’ll get through this together.
